<TITLE> Govt needs to provide judicial magistrates with staffers, vehicles by Apr22 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 05 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court Wednesday ordered the government to provide the judicial magistrates with supporting staffers, vehicles and other needs by April 22. The court asked the government to complete all necessary measures "as soon as possible" and submit detailed reports on or before April 22. A seven-strong full bench of the Appellate Division chaired by chief justice Md Ruhul Amin made the order and adjourned proceedings until then. Attorney general Fida M Kamal submitted gazette documents tied to the matter and said: "The government promulgated the recruitment rules on March 3." The court said: "The government has published the gazette, that's alright. But when will the rest of the activities be completed?" The attorney general said: "The government is working to execute the pending stuffs tied to the separation of the judiciary." Speaking to bdnews24.com immediately after the court proceedings, the attorney general said the government was doing everything in line with the court order. On Dec 12, the Supreme Court ordered the government to provide judicial magistrates with supporting staffers, vehicles and other requirements in line with an Oct 28 letter of the Ministry of Establishment. The caretaker government officially announced separation of the judiciary from the executive branch on Nov 1, 2007. bdnews24.
